Spore Cough	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MuSporeRaceTrait.SpecialAttack.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once every 1d4 rounds a mu spore can release a cloud of burrowing spores. This spore cough is treated as a %1-foot-cone breath weapon. The burrowing spores deal %2d%3 points of damage to all creatures and structures in the area, or half damage to any creatures that make a Reflex save (DC %4).|BreathWeaponCone|BreathWeaponDice|BreathWeaponDamageDie|BreathWeaponDC	KEY:Mu Spore ~ Spore Cough				DEFINE:BreathWeaponCone|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDice|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDamageDie|0	DEFINE:BreathWeaponDC|0		BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponCone|100	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDice|20	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDamageDie|8|TYPE=Base	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDC|DefaultDCCon	BONUS:VAR|BreathWeaponDC|2|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Ability Focus (Breath Weapon)					ABILITY:Ability Focus|AUTOMATIC|Breath Weapon									SOURCEPAGE:ELH
Improved Grab	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MuSporeRaceTrait.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Improved Grab	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If a mu spore hits with a tendril, it deals normal damage and attempts to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. Improved grab works only against Gargantuan and smaller opponents. The mu spore has the option to conduct the grapple normally, transfer the victim to its mouth as a free action, or simply use its tendril to hold the opponent. Each successful grapple check it makes during successive rounds automatically deals the damage given for the tendril.	KEY:Mu Spore ~ Improved Grab																											SOURCEPAGE:ELH
Swallow Whole	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MuSporeRaceTrait.SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Swallow Whole	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If the mu spore begins its turn with an opponent held in its mouth, it can attempt a new grapple check (as though attempting to pin the opponent). If it succeeds, it swallows its prey and the opponent takes bite damage. A swallowed creature takes the twice the damage given for the mu spore's bite every round. A swallowed creature is considered grappled, while the creature that did the swallowing is not. A swallowed creature can try to cut its way free with any light piercing or slashing weapon, if it can deal 33 points of damage in this fashion, or it can just try to escape the grapple. If the swallowed creature choose the latter course, success puts it back in the mu spores mouth, where it may be bitten or swallowed again.	KEY:Mu Spore ~ Swallow Whole																											SOURCEPAGE:ELH
Sticky	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:MuSporeRaceTrait.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Sticky tendrils cover a mu spore, many more than the four main tendrils it uses for combat. Any creature that touches or successfully attacks a mu spore with a melee weapon is subject to a free improved grab check by the mu spore, as if the mu spore had successfully attacked the creature with a tendril. A creature wielding a melee weapon must immediately relinquish its grip on its weapon, or proceed with the grapple check. If the subject relinquishes its grip on its weapon, the weapon is swallowed the following round. Creatures who attack the mu spore in melee without a weapon they can release (such as those with natural attacks only, do not have this option).	KEY:Mu Spore ~ Sticky																											SOURCEPAGE:ELH
																																
